    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-05T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="1153"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1153">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Strong</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="96" xml:id="d1153fn96">Repeated to the Consul General at
                        Taipei as No. 434.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-05T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 5, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>TelCan 745. Re Taipei’s 660, Nov 4, rptd Chungking 216, Hong Kong 66, and
                        AirAtt<note n="97" xml:id="d1153fn97">Air Attaché.</note> Taipei’s Oil, Nov
                        5,<note n="98" xml:id="d1153fn98">Latter not printed.</note> being rptd
                    Chungking Hong Kong Shanghai.</p>
                <p>You are instructed seek appointment with FonMin<note n="99" xml:id="d1153fn99"
                        >George Kung-chao Yeh.</note> and inform him orally of receipt this info
                    from CAF. You shld state US Govt trusts that this info inaccurate or that it
                    represents attitude irresponsible elements Taipei and not considered view Chi
                    Govt, and you shld request assurances this regard. You shld add that US Govt wld
                    view with serious concern any declared intention Chi Govt bomb US vessels either
                    on high seas (Formosan Straits) or within Chi terr waters, whether those waters
                    controlled by Natl Govt or Chi Commies; that US Govt wld consider any unprovoked
                    attack on US shipping as act of utmost gravity and one not in consonance with
                    relations friendly nations.</p>
                <p>ConGen Taipei shld orally inform Chen Cheng<note n="1" xml:id="d1153fn1">Governor
                        of Taiwan.</note> above representations being made Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
